			<ns0:name>stich...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/111656935494976488934/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">LLVM's FastISel code generator produces problematic code in some cases that is incorrectly sandboxed on x86_64, usually leading to a segmentation fault when the sequence is executed.

This issue is addressed in the regular code generator, in X86DAGToDAGISel::LegalizeAddressingModeForNaCl().

The problem can be seen on the spec2k benchmarks gcc and crafty, when forcing fast-isel e.g. by modifying pnacl/driver/pnacl-translate.py to set default FAST_TRANSLATION=1 and uncommenting the &amp;quot;-fast-isel&amp;quot; flag in the LLC_FLAGS_FAST_X8664 definition.
